cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the development of a deep spiking neural network enabled by a neuromimetic device, specifically a magnetic tunnel junction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the device in hardware, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), cs.EM (Electronic Materials), or cs.AR (Architecture). Finally, the paper focuses on classification tasks, which could also place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category.
